body: Too much inconsistency in this kind of crap. One, divine luck Bell would avoid this kind of problem. Two, a goddess can't be impregnated by a mortal. Three, Hestia is a goddess who takes a vow of chastity for millions of years, as if she could succumb to the temptation of becoming like Freya and sleeping with a man she's not sure she loves on the spur of the moment, LMAO... In fact she would kick him out right away by insulting him and would surely prefer to use her divine power and be sent back to heaven, rather than lose her precious virginity and be defiled by such a man, just like Artemis who is really scary when she is angry. Don't underestimate the holy virgins, they are sexually inaccessible even for the gods and have escaped any kind of rape.
